HEADWORD: Nous
<hw>Nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>noy^s</grk> mind.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Intellect; understanding;
talent; -- used humorously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>The reason; the highest
intellect; God regarded as the World Reason.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

